README for wikipedia-tracker
============================

wikipedia-tracker is a set of tools to visualize your visited Wikipedia pages
in a nice directed graph.

How to use wikipedia-tracker
============================

- Run wp-tracker-proxy.rb on your local machine.

- Configure your browser to use localhost:8080 as HTTP proxy.

- Surf around on Wikipedia.

- Reset your HTTP proxy configuration.

- Use wpt-make-digraph.rb to postprocess the resulting .csv file(s) into .dot file(s).

- Use graphviz to render .dot files to images.

Requirements
============

- Ruby 1.8
- Log4r Ruby module
- graphviz if you want to visualize the results
